        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali115-kilavi">itu talaivi kaḷavu veḷippaṭṭateṉṟu añcit tōḻikkuc colla emar niṉṉai avarkkē koṭukkac cūḻntāreṉac colli accam nīkkiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali115">
                <l>tōḻināṅ, kāṇāmai yuṇṭa kaṭuṅkaḷḷai meykūra </l>
                <l>nāṇātu ceṉṟu naṭuṅka vuraittāṅkuk </l>
                <l>karantatūuṅ kaiyoṭu kōṭpaṭṭāṅ kaṇṭāynam </l>
                <l>pulliṉat tāya makaṉcūṭi vantatōr </l>
                <l>mullai yorukāḻuṅ kaṇṇiyu melliyāl </l>
                <l>kūntaluṭ peytu muṭittēṉmaṟ ṟōḻiyāy </l>
                <l>veṇṇe yuraii viritta katuppōṭē </l>
                <l>yaṉṉaiyu mattaṉu millarā yāynāṇa </l>
                <l>vaṉṉaimuṉ vīḻntaṉṟap pū;</l>
                <l rend="space">ataṉai, viṉavaluñ ceyyāḷ ciṉavaluñ ceyyā </l>
                <l>ṇeruppukkai toṭṭavar pōla vitirttiṭṭu </l>
                <l>nīṅkip puṟaṅkaṭaip pōyiṉāḷ yāṉumeṉ </l>
                <l>cāntuḷar kūḻai muṭiyā nilantāḻnta </l>
                <l>pūṅkarai nīlan taḻīit taḷarpolkip </l>
                <l>pāṅkaruṅ kāṉat toḷittē ṉataṟkellā </l>
                <l>vīṅkeva ṉañcu vatu;</l>
                <l rend="space">añcal,  avaṉkaṇṇi nīpuṉaintā yāyi ṉamaru </l>
                <l>mavaṉka ṇaṭaicūḻntār niṉṉai yakaṉkaṇ </l>
                <l>varaippiṉ maṇaṟṟāḻap peytu tiraippil </l>
                <l>vatuvaiyu mīṅkē yayarpa vatuvēyā </l>
                <l>malkaluñ cūḻnta viṉai.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>“O friend, see [how] we underwent all that [we] had hidden being caught by the hand,</l>
                <l>as if, when the body was full of fierce toddy that had been drunk without [anybody] seeing,</l>
                <l>going without shame [and] talking while trembling. </l>
                <l>[You with] soft nature, the one strand of jasmine and the chaplet </l>
                <l>that had come from our herder’s son wearing [them]</l>
                <l>we had put [them] in [our] tresses [and] tied [them]. Friend,</l>
                <l>from the hair that my mother rubbed with oil [and] spread out</l>
                <l>so that my mother was ashamed, as mother and father were not there,</l>
                <l corresp="1-9">that flower fell down before mother.</l>
                <l>That, she did not ask about [it] and she did not become angry.</l>
                <l>As if [her] hand had touched fire she shuddered,</l>
                <l>left [and] went through the outer gate. And I, </l>
                <l>clutching a blue lotus from the flower shore , that had sunk to the ground, </l>
                <l>not being tied to my short hair in which sandal paste was drying, faltering, turning weak</l>
                <l>I hid in the neighbouring forest difficult [to enter].” – “What is there</l>
                <l corresp="10-16">to be afraid of here because of that?</l>
                <l>Don’t fear, when you were decorated with his chaplet, our people</l>
                <l>considered giving you to him. They pour sand down</l>
                <l>in the region of vast area and prepare the wedding here</l>
                <l>in [this] location. Just that is</l>
                <l corresp="17-21">the work that had been considered all night.”</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
